# Spot (Android) ‚ÄĒ Project Rules

You are building the **Android port of Spot**, a social place-discovery app, from the specs in `PRD/`.
The full product spec lives in `PRD/` (start at `PRD/README.md`). The build sequence and
agent-sized task list live in `PRD/18-build-order.md`. **Read the relevant PRD doc before
implementing a feature** ‚ÄĒ do not guess contracts.

## Non-negotiable golden rules

1. **Same backend, same contracts.** Android talks to the *same* Supabase project as iOS
   (`aeurigbbohyxvtsfiyul`). Never fork the schema. All access goes through the RPCs/tables in
   `PRD/03-data-model.md` and `PRD/04-backend-api.md`. **RLS is authoritative** ‚ÄĒ never rely on
   client-only authorization.
2. **Supabase is the only data plane** for users, spots, media, social data. Firebase = analytics/
   crash/App Check only. Never add a second datastore or a parallel upload path.
3. **Every uploaded image must pass moderation** (`moderate-image` edge function) before it becomes
   an approved, publicly-referenced asset. No client-only bypass.
4. **Safety features ship in v1 and are non-negotiable:** terms agreement before registration,
   image + text moderation, report content, report + block users, content filtering. See
   `PRD/13-moderation-safety.md`.
5. **Preserve limits/gating exactly** so both platforms behave identically against shared data:
   feed page 24; post free 1 image/1 vibe, Pro 5/5; bookmark free cap 50; vibe length 2‚Äď30;
   publish timeout 90s; OTP 6 digits, resend 30s; map cap 250. Pull the authoritative numbers from
   the PRD, never hardcode a guess.
6. **Never embed the service-role key.** Only the anon/publishable key ships in the client.
7. **Sign in with Apple ‚Üí Google Sign-In** is the sanctioned platform swap (via supabase-kt OAuth).
   Email/password + email OTP remains the primary flow. Any OAuth account without a username hits
   the post-auth username gate.

## Stack (do not substitute without a note in the PR)

- **Kotlin + Jetpack Compose** (Material 3, custom light-only theme).
- **MVVM/MVI**: ViewModel + `StateFlow<UiState>`; one-shot effects via `Channel`/`SharedFlow`.
- **Hilt** for DI.
- **Navigation-Compose** + custom bottom bar (5 tabs) + overlay host for deep-link/paywall overlays.
- **Coroutines + Flow** for async.
- **supabase-kt** (`gotrue`, `postgrest`, `storage`, `functions`, `realtime`).
- **Coil** with an auth-aware fetcher for signed URLs.
- **Google Maps Compose** + FusedLocationProvider.
- **Google Play Billing v6+** for Pro.
- **FCM** (+ `NotificationManagerCompat` local notifications).
- Persistence: **DataStore** (prefs/search history), files/Room (drafts), supabase-kt encrypted
  session storage.

## Architecture rules

- Layering is strict: `UI (Compose) ‚Üí ViewModel ‚Üí Repository/Service (typed interfaces) ‚Üí Supabase`.
- **No business logic in composables.** No Supabase calls from composables or ViewModels directly ‚ÄĒ
  always through a repository interface.
- Repositories are **interfaces with fakes** so ViewModels are unit-testable with no live Supabase,
  no real billing, no real OAuth.
- Every user-facing flow explicitly handles **loading / empty / error / unauthenticated** states.
- Keep the current user's `liked` / `bookmarked` / `blocked` / Pro sets in a **shared session
  holder** so feed, map, search, and profile stay consistent.
- Package layout follows `PRD/01-architecture-android.md` (`core/`, `data/`, `feature/`,
  `navigation/`, `di/`). Do not invent a different structure.

## DTO / data conventions

- DTOs use **snake_case field names** matching Postgres (no global snake_case conversion). Domain
  models (`Spot`, `User`) are assembled in code from DTOs ‚ÄĒ see `PRD/04`, `PRD/06`, `PRD/10`.
- Map Postgres types: `uuid`‚ÜíString, `double precision`‚ÜíDouble, `timestamptz`‚ÜíISO-8601 String,
  `uuid[]`‚ÜíList<String>, `jsonb`‚ÜíJsonObject.
- Profile writes go through `sync_current_user_v1`, **not** a direct upsert.
- Set `platform = "android"` on `reports` and `user_terms_acceptances`.

## Coding conventions

- Reuse shared components (`SpotCard`, vibe chip, avatar, empty/skeleton views, paywall sheet,
  report/block flows). Do not re-implement `SpotCard` per screen.
- Use `Modifier.testTag(...)` with the **iOS identifier strings** (`navigation.homeTab`,
  `home.feedRoot`, `welcome.screen`, ‚Ä¶) so a shared test vocabulary works.
- Design tokens (colors, spacing, radius, type) come only from the central theme built from
  `PRD/02-design-system.md`. Never inline hex colors in feature code.
- Optimistic like/bookmark/delete with rollback on failure.
- Emit feed events via a lightweight coalescing service (`record_feed_event_v1`).

## Safety, security & logging

- Auth/terms gating runs **before** any sensitive network/DB/posting action.
- Treat 401/403 and empty RLS-filtered results as expected when unauthenticated/unauthorized.
- **Never log PII, tokens, or raw image bytes.** Use the structured logger with per-area categories.
- Downscale images to ‚Č§1600px longest edge, JPEG ~0.8, before upload.
- Cache signed spot-image URLs until near their 7-day expiry.

## Definition of done (every feature task)

- Matches the relevant `PRD/NN-*.md` contract, states, copy, and constants.
- Loading/empty/error/unauthenticated states implemented.
- Unit tests for ViewModel logic using fakes (see `PRD/17` high-value scenarios).
- No hardcoded secrets; anon key only; RLS relied on for authz.
- `./gradlew assembleDebug` compiles; lint clean; no new PII in logs.
- Test tags match the iOS vocabulary where practical.

## When unsure

- The PRD is the source of truth for behavior; the **live Supabase schema** is the source of truth
  for contracts. If a contract seems ambiguous, re-read `PRD/03`/`PRD/04` before inventing one.
- Anything marked **[ANDROID DECISION]** in the PRD already has a recommended default ‚ÄĒ follow it.
